lessons.theory:
## Rust Types
Rust is statically typed. Types are often inferred, but sometimes explicit.

```rust
// Integers (i32, u32, i64, etc.)
let age: u32 = 25;  // Unsigned 32-bit

// Floats (f32, f64)
let pi: f64 = 3.14159;

// Boolean
let is_active: bool = true;

// Character (4 bytes, Unicode)
let emoji: char = '😻';

// Tuples
let point: (i32, f64) = (10, 3.5);
```

