lessons.theory:
## Keeping References Valid
Rust must guarantee that all references are valid (no dangling pointers).

When a function takes multiple references, the compiler sometimes needs help knowing how long they live. We use **lifetimes** (annotated with `'a`).

```rust
// 'a means "both x and y must live as long as the returned reference"
fn longest<'a>(x: &'a str, y: &'a str) -> &'a str {
    if x.len() > y.len() { x } else { y }
}
```

