    handle.join().unwrap();
}

lessons.theory:
## File I/O in Rust
Rust's `std::fs` module provides functionality for interacting with the file system.

```rust
use std::fs;

// Read entire file to string
let contents = fs::read_to_string("file.txt").expect("Failed to read file");

// Write string to file (overwrites)
fs::write("output.txt", "Hello World!").expect("Failed to write");
```
Note the use of `.expect()`. File operations return a `Result` enum because they can fail (e.g., file not found, permission denied).

